{
    "name": "Harbor Seal",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Harbor Seal",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Harbor seals are the most common seals found in Golarion and famous for their soft, furry bodies. They're vicious hunters underwater, but typically shy of humanoids on the surface, preferring to hide among the waves rather than face down what seems to be a terrifying land predator.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Howl of the Wild",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Howl of the Wild pg. 178",
                        "alt": "Howl of the Wild pg. 178",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 226
                    },
                    "page": 178,
                    "errata": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "2.1",
                        "alt": "2.1",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 226
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Seal",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Seals are semi-aquatic carnivorous mammals found on beaches across Golarion. They're known for their extraordinary hunting skills, using their sensitive whiskers to detect the movement and the size of fish they're hunting, even allowing them to locate hidden prey",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Howl of the Wild",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Howl of the Wild pg. 178",
                        "alt": "Howl of the Wild pg. 178",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 226
                    },
                    "page": 178,
